{"title_page": "Destiny Etiko", "text_new": "{{short description|Nigerian actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Destiny Etiko\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Destiny Etiko\n|nationality = [[Nigerian]]\n|birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|8|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Enugu State]], [[Nigeria]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Nnamdi!\nAzikiwe University]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 2011-Present \n| children           = \n| website            = \n}}\n \n'''Destiny Etiko''' (born August 12, 1989) is a Nigerian actress who won the ''City People Movie Award for Most Promising Actress of the Year (English)'' at the [[City People Entertainment Awards]] in 2016.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Early life and education==\nEtiko was born in [[Udi, Enugu|Udi]], a village located precisely in [[Enugu state]], a southeastern geographical area of [[Nigeria]] occupied predominantly by the [[igbo people]] of Nigeria. \nEtiko received both her primary and secondary school education in Enugu State where she obtained her ''First School Leaving Certificate'' and the ''[[West African Senior School Certificate Examination|West African Senior School Certificate]].'' Etiko in bid to obtain a university degree relocated to [[Anambra state]] then applied to study Theater Arts In [[Nnamdi Azikiwe University]] located in [[Awka]]. Etiko was accepted and granted admission and eventually graduate with a degree in Theater Arts.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/08/actress-etiko-destiny-stuns-in-bikinis-to-mark-birthday/|title=Actress Etiko Destiny stuns in bikinis to mark birthday|date=2015-08-12|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nEtiko described in an interview with [[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]], a Nigerian print media, that after registering with the [[Actors Guild of Nigeria]] she ventured into the Nigerian movie industry commonly known as [[Nollywood]] in 2011 and described her experience then as a difficult one because she had to combine her acting career with her school recruitments as she was still a student at the time. Etiko's career received prominence after she featured in a movie titled ''Idemili'' which was produced in 2012 by Ernest Obi but was not released until 2014. Her role in the movie earned her a [[City People Entertainment Awards]] nomination. Before her role in the movie titled ''Idemili'', Etiko had appeared in other movies although did not receive prominent roles in them.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Award==\nEtiko won the ''City People Movie Award for Most Promising Actress of the Year (English)'' at the [[City People Entertainment Awards]] in 2016.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.withinnigeria.com/amp/2019/08/12/nigerian-actress-destiny-etiko-career-personal-life-childhood-and-early-life/|title=Nigerian actress, Destiny Etiko: Career, Personal Life, Childhood And Early Life|date=2019-08-12|website=Within Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Endorsement==\nIn 2019, Etiko became a brand ambassador for ''Kesie Virgin Hair'' organization.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talkglitz.tv/destiny-etiko-lands-new-endorsement-deal-with-kesie_virgin-hair/|title=Destiny Etiko Lands New Endorsement Deal With Kesie_Virgin Hair|last=Savvy|first=Blessing ObiezeContributor at TalkGlitz MediaDiscreet WriterAvid ReaderCreativity|date=2019-11-05|website=talkGlitz.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://naijadiary.ng/2019/11/05/destiny-etiko-signs-endorsement-deal-with-kesie_virgin-hair/|title=Destiny Etiko Signs Endorsement Deal With Kesie_Virgin Hair|last=Ejiogu|first=Chinecherem|date=2019-11-05|website=NaijaDiary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nUnlike what has become the norm in the Nigerian movie industry which is relocating to [[Lagos state]] in order to succeed as a creative, Etiko who was born in [[Enugu state]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/10/etiko-destiny-touted-best-figure-nollywood/|title=Etiko Destiny touted with best figure in Nollywood|date=2017-10-29|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> still resides there and has been living there throughout the course of her acting career. Etiko in an interview affirmed that she had been a victim of sexual harassment against women by male movie producers who are by far the majority as pertains movie productions in Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/04/sleeping-around-is-not-a-guarantee-to-getting-movie-roles/|title='Sleeping around is not a guarantee to getting movie roles'|date=2015-04-04|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> Etiko in 2019 gifted her mum an apartment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allure.vanguardngr.com/2018/12/actress-destiny-etiko-gifts-mother-with-new-home-as-she-marks-birthday/|title=Actress Destiny Etiko gifts mother new home as she marks birthday|last=RITA|date=2018-12-28|website=Vanguard Allure|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.legit.ng/1212348-actress-destiny-etiko-gifts-mum-a-house-birthday.html|title=Curvy actress Destiny Etiko surprises her mother with a house on birthday|last=Durojaiye|first=Seun|date=2018-12-29|website=www.legit.ng|language=en|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tori.ng/news/115357/curvy-actress-destiny-etiko-lands-in-hospital-phot.html|title=Curvy Actress, Destiny Etiko Lands In Hospital (Photo)|last=George|last2=George|date=2019-01-30|website=Tori.ng|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> and praised her for supporting her decision to become an actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailyadvent.com/ettmt/2018/12/28/omg-see-the-mansion-actress-destiny-etiko-builds-for-her-mother-as-birthday-gift/|title=OMG!! See The Mansion Actress Destiny Etiko Builds For Her Mother As Birthday Gift|date=2018-12-28|website=Daily Advent Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> Her father on the other hand had vehemently opposed her decision to become an actress at the initial time.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n*''The prince & I (2019)''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://nlist.ng//people/destiny-etiko-1969/|title=Destiny Etiko - nlist {{!}} Nollywood, Nigerian Movies & Casting|website=nlist.ng|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n*''Heart of Love (2019)''\n*''My sisters love (2019)''\n*''Poor Billionaire (2019)''\n*''Virgin goddess (2019)''\n*''Queen of love (2019)''\n*''The Sacred Cowry (2019)''\n*''The Return of Ezendiala (2019)''\n*''Barren Kingdom (2019)''\n*''Pains of the Orphan (2019)''\n*''Clap of Royalty (2019)''\n*''The Hidden Sin (2019)''\n*''Family Yoke (2019)''\n*''King\u2019s Word (2019)''\n*''Sound of Evil (2019)''\n*''My Private Part (2019)'' as Stella\n*''Power of Royalty (2019)''\n*''Sunset of Love (2019)''\n*''London Prince (2019)''\n*''Woman of Power (2019)''\n*''Tears of Regret (2018)''\n*''Evil Seekers (2017)''\n*''Fear of a Woman (2016)''\n*''3 Days to Wed (2016)''<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*''The Storm (2016)''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.instagram.com/destinyetikoofficial/?hl=en Official social media page]\n\n{{IMDb Name|9313348}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Etiko, Destiny}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian actresses]]\n[[Category:Igbo actresses]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:People from Udi]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Destiny Etiko\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Destiny Etiko\n|nationality = [[Nigerian]]\n|birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|8|12}}\n| birth_place        = [[Enugu State]], [[Nigeria]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Nnamdi Azikiwe University]]\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 2011-Present \n| children           = \n| website            = \n}}\n \n'''Destiny Etiko''' (born August 12, 1989) is a Nigerian actress who won the ''City People Movie Award for Most Promising Actress of the Year (English)'' at the [[City People Entertainment Awards]] in 2016.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Early life and education==\nEtiko was born in [[Udi, Enugu|Udi]], a village located precisely in [[Enugu state]], a southeastern geographical area of [[Nigeria]] occupied predominantly by the [[igbo people]] of Nigeria. \nEtiko received both her primary and secondary school education in Enugu State where she obtained her ''First School Leaving Certificate'' and the ''[[West African Senior School Certificate Examination|West African Senior School Certificate]].'' Etiko in bid to obtain a university degree relocated to [[Anambra state]] then applied to study Theater Arts In [[Nnamdi Azikiwe University]] located in [[Awka]]. Etiko was accepted and granted admission and eventually graduate with a degree in Theater Arts.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/08/actress-etiko-destiny-stuns-in-bikinis-to-mark-birthday/|title=Actress Etiko Destiny stuns in bikinis to mark birthday|date=2015-08-12|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nEtiko described in an interview with [[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]], a Nigerian print media, that after registering with the [[Actors Guild of Nigeria]] she ventured into the Nigerian movie industry commonly known as [[Nollywood]] in 2011 and described her experience then as a difficult one because she had to combine her acting career with her school recruitments as she was still a student at the time. Etiko's career received prominence after she featured in a movie titled ''Idemili'' which was produced in 2012 by Ernest Obi but was not released until 2014. Her role in the movie earned her a [[City People Entertainment Awards]] nomination. Before her role in the movie titled ''Idemili'', Etiko had appeared in other movies although did not receive prominent roles in them.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Award==\nEtiko won the ''City People Movie Award for Most Promising Actress of the Year (English)'' at the [[City People Entertainment Awards]] in 2016.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.withinnigeria.com/amp/2019/08/12/nigerian-actress-destiny-etiko-career-personal-life-childhood-and-early-life/|title=Nigerian actress, Destiny Etiko: Career, Personal Life, Childhood And Early Life|date=2019-08-12|website=Within Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Endorsement==\nIn 2019, Etiko became a brand ambassador for ''Kesie Virgin Hair'' organization.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://talkglitz.tv/destiny-etiko-lands-new-endorsement-deal-with-kesie_virgin-hair/|title=Destiny Etiko Lands New Endorsement Deal With Kesie_Virgin Hair|last=Savvy|first=Blessing ObiezeContributor at TalkGlitz MediaDiscreet WriterAvid ReaderCreativity|date=2019-11-05|website=talkGlitz.tv|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://naijadiary.ng/2019/11/05/destiny-etiko-signs-endorsement-deal-with-kesie_virgin-hair/|title=Destiny Etiko Signs Endorsement Deal With Kesie_Virgin Hair|last=Ejiogu|first=Chinecherem|date=2019-11-05|website=NaijaDiary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nUnlike what has become the norm in the Nigerian movie industry which is relocating to [[Lagos state]] in order to succeed as a creative, Etiko who was born in [[Enugu state]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/10/etiko-destiny-touted-best-figure-nollywood/|title=Etiko Destiny touted with best figure in Nollywood|date=2017-10-29|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" /> still resides there and has been living there throughout the course of her acting career. Etiko in an interview affirmed that she had been a victim of sexual harassment against women by male movie producers who are by far the majority as pertains movie productions in Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/04/sleeping-around-is-not-a-guarantee-to-getting-movie-roles/|title='Sleeping around is not a guarantee to getting movie roles'|date=2015-04-04|website=Vanguard News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> Etiko in 2019 gifted her mum an apartment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allure.vanguardngr.com/2018/12/actress-destiny-etiko-gifts-mother-with-new-home-as-she-marks-birthday/|title=Actress Destiny Etiko gifts mother new home as she marks birthday|last=RITA|date=2018-12-28|website=Vanguard Allure|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.legit.ng/1212348-actress-destiny-etiko-gifts-mum-a-house-birthday.html|title=Curvy actress Destiny Etiko surprises her mother with a house on birthday|last=Durojaiye|first=Seun|date=2018-12-29|website=www.legit.ng|language=en|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tori.ng/news/115357/curvy-actress-destiny-etiko-lands-in-hospital-phot.html|title=Curvy Actress, Destiny Etiko Lands In Hospital (Photo)|last=George|last2=George|date=2019-01-30|website=Tori.ng|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> and praised her for supporting her decision to become an actress.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dailyadvent.com/ettmt/2018/12/28/omg-see-the-mansion-actress-destiny-etiko-builds-for-her-mother-as-birthday-gift/|title=OMG!! See The Mansion Actress Destiny Etiko Builds For Her Mother As Birthday Gift|date=2018-12-28|website=Daily Advent Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref> Her father on the other hand had vehemently opposed her decision to become an actress at the initial time.\n\n==Selected filmography==\n*''The prince & I (2019)''<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://nlist.ng//people/destiny-etiko-1969/|title=Destiny Etiko - nlist {{!}} Nollywood, Nigerian Movies & Casting|website=nlist.ng|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-12-26}}</ref>\n*''Heart of Love (2019)''\n*''My sisters love (2019)''\n*''Poor Billionaire (2019)''\n*''Virgin goddess (2019)''\n*''Queen of love (2019)''\n*''The Sacred Cowry (2019)''\n*''The Return of Ezendiala (2019)''\n*''Barren Kingdom (2019)''\n*''Pains of the Orphan (2019)''\n*''Clap of Royalty (2019)''\n*''The Hidden Sin (2019)''\n*''Family Yoke (2019)''\n*''King\u2019s Word (2019)''\n*''Sound of Evil (2019)''\n*''My Private Part (2019)'' as Stella\n*''Power of Royalty (2019)''\n*''Sunset of Love (2019)''\n*''London Prince (2019)''\n*''Woman of Power (2019)''\n*''Tears of Regret (2018)''\n*''Evil Seekers (2017)''\n*''Fear of a Woman (2016)''\n*''3 Days to Wed (2016)''<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*''The Storm (2016)''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.instagram.com/destinyetikoofficial/?hl=en Official social media page]\n\n{{IMDb Name|9313348}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Etiko, Destiny}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian actresses]]\n[[Category:Igbo actresses]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:People from Udi]]\n", "name_user": "76.89.189.255", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destiny_Etiko"}
{"title_page": "Eric Anderson (teacher)", "text_new": "{{other people||Eric Anderson (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name = Sir Eric Anderson\n| honorific_suffix = {{postnominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KT|FRSE}}\n| image = \n| birth_name = William Eric Kinloch Anderson\n| birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1936|5|27}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2020|04|22|1936|5|27}}\n| spouse = Poppy Mason\n| children = 2\n| education = [[George Watson's College]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of St Andrews]] (MA)<br/>[[Balliol College, Oxford]] (MLitt)\n| occupation = Academic\n}}\n\n'''Sir William Eric Kinloch Anderson''', {{postnominals|country=GBR|size=100%|sep=,|KT|FRSE}} (27 May 1936 \u2013 22 April 2020),<ref name=Birth>{{cite news|title=Birthday's today|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/archive/2013-5-27.html|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=24 May 2014|date=27 May 2013|quote=Sir Eric Anderson, Provost of Eton College, 2000\u201309, 77 years old}}</ref><ref>[[David Anderson, Baron Anderson of Ipswich|David Anderson]], [https://twitter.com/bricksilk/status/1253244809931894786 note of death], 23 April 2020 (twitter)</ref> was a teacher and educator, who was [[Provost of Eton|Provost]] of [[Eton College]] from September 2000 to 30 January 2009.<ref>[http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/a/15159/(William)%20Eric%20Kinloch+ANDERSON.aspx Profile: Sir Eric Anderson, KT, FRSE], [[Debrett's]].</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAnderson was schooled at [[George Watson's College]], [[Edinburgh]] and graduated from the [[University of St Andrews]] with [[First class honours degree#First-class honours|First-Class Honours]] in English Language and Literature, and subsequently as an [[Master of Letters|MLitt]] from [[Balliol College]], [[University of Oxford|Oxford]].\n\nIn his early career, Anderson taught at [[Fettes College]], [[Edinburgh]], and at [[Gordonstoun]], where he taught [[Charles, Prince of Wales|Prince Charles]]. He moved to be headmaster at [[Abingdon School]] (1970\u201375), [[Shrewsbury School]] (1975\u201380) and  [[Eton College]] (1980\u201394) and he was Rector of [[Lincoln College, Oxford]] (1994\u20132000). He was chairman of the [[National Lottery (United Kingdom)|Heritage Lottery Fund]] (1998\u20132001), and Provost of [[Eton College]] (2000\u20132009).\n\nAt Fettes, he was [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] [[Tony Blair]]'s housemaster. Blair subsequently named Anderson in a 1997 advertising campaign run by the [[Teacher Training Agency]], entitled 'No one forgets a good teacher'. Because Anderson was Head Master of Eton while [[David Cameron]] and [[Boris Johnson]] were there, he was involved in the education of the heir to the British throne and three British Prime Ministers, as well as [[Justin Welby]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]].\n\nThe Clarendon Press published Anderson's edition of [[The Journal of Sir Walter Scott]] in 1972 and he became a trustee of Scott's [[Abbotsford House|Abbotsford]] during its refurbishment. He was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Edinburgh]] in 1985 and, in 2002, he was appointed a Knight of the [[Order of the Thistle]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=56780 |date=12 December 2002 |pages=15113\u201315114 }}</ref> \n\nHe retired as Provost of Eton at the end of January 2009, and was succeeded by [[William Waldegrave, Baron Waldegrave of North Hill|William Waldegrave]].\n\nHis other positions included: [[Visitor]] at [[Harris Manchester College, Oxford]]; Member of the Visiting Committee of Harvard University Memorial Church; [[trustee]] of the [[Royal Collection Trust]]; and Chairman of [[Cumberland Lodge]]. He has honorary degrees from the [[University of St Andrews]], Hull, Siena, Birmingham, the [[University of Aberdeen]] and Buckingham.<ref>{{cite web|title=HRH The Duchess of Rothesay joins University 'family'|url=http://www.abdn.ac.uk/news/details-13923.php|publisher=University of Aberdeen}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAnderson was the son of William James Kinloch Anderson and Margaret Gouinlock Harper. He was married to Elizabeth (Poppy) Anderson, daughter of William and Mary Mason of Skipton.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fieldtree.blogspot.com/2012/12/sir-william-eric-kinloch-anderson.html|title=Sir William Eric Kinloch Anderson|last=Field|first=Ron|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-02}}</ref> Their son is [[David Anderson (barrister)|David Anderson Q.C]] (Lord Anderson of Ipswich) and their daughter Kate is married to [[Will Gompertz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/will-gompertz-we-are-all-artists-we-just-have-to-believe-it-that-s-what-artists-do-10389894.html|title=Will Gompertz: 'We are all artists. We just have to believe it. That's what artists do'|newspaper=The Evening Standard}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Michael William McCrum]]\n| title=[[List of head masters of Eton College|Head Master of Eton College]]\n| years=1980\u20131994\n| after=[[John Lewis (headmaster)|John Lewis]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Maurice Shock]]\n| title=[[Rector (college)|Rector]] of [[Lincoln College, Oxford]]\n| years=1994\u20132000 \n| after=[[Paul Langford]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Provost of Eton]]\n| before=[[Antony Acland|Sir Antony Acland]]\n| after= [[William Waldegrave, Baron Waldegrave of North Hill|William Waldegrave]]\n| years=2000\u20132009\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Members of the Order of the Thistle}}\n{{Eton Head Masters}}\n{{Provosts of Eton College}}\n{{Rectors of Lincoln College, Oxford}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Anderson, Eric}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of St Andrews]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Balliol College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:People educated at George Watson's College]]\n[[Category:Scottish schoolteachers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of Lincoln College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society of Edinburgh]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Thistle]]\n[[Category:Headmasters of Shrewsbury School]]\n[[Category:Rectors of Lincoln College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:Head Masters of Eton College]]\n[[Category:Heads of Abingdon School]]\n[[Category:Staff of Abingdon School]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people||Eric Anderson (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix =\n| name = Sir Eric Anderson\n| honorific_suffix = {{postnominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KT|FRSE}}\n| image = \n| birth_name = William Eric Kinloch Anderson\n| birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1936|5|27}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|2020|04|22|1936|5|27}}\n| spouse = Poppy Mason\n| children = 2\n| education = [[George Watson's College]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of St Andrews]] (MA)<br/>[[Balliol College, Oxford]] (MLitt)\n| occupation = Academic\n}}\n\n'''Sir William Eric Kinloch Anderson''', {{postnominals|country=GBR|size=100%|sep=,|KT|FRSE}} (27 May 1936\u201322 April 2020),<ref name=Birth>{{cite news|title=Birthday's today|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/archive/2013-5-27.html|newspaper=The Telegraph|accessdate=24 May 2014|date=27 May 2013|quote=Sir Eric Anderson, Provost of Eton College, 2000\u201309, 77 years old}}</ref><ref>[[David Anderson, Baron Anderson of Ipswich|David Anderson]], [https://twitter.com/bricksilk/status/1253244809931894786 note of death], 23 April 2020 (twitter)</ref> was a teacher and educator, who was [[Provost of Eton|Provost]] of [[Eton College]] from September 2000 to 30 January 2009.<ref>[http://www.debretts.com/people/biographies/browse/a/15159/(William)%20Eric%20Kinloch+ANDERSON.aspx Profile: Sir Eric Anderson, KT, FRSE], [[Debrett's]].</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nAnderson was schooled at [[George Watson's College]], [[Edinburgh]] and graduated from the [[University of St Andrews]] with [[First class honours degree#First-class honours|First-Class Honours]] in English Language and Literature, and subsequently as an [[Master of Letters|MLitt]] from [[Balliol College]], [[University of Oxford|Oxford]].\n\nIn his early career, Anderson taught at [[Fettes College]], [[Edinburgh]], and at [[Gordonstoun]], where he taught [[Charles, Prince of Wales|Prince Charles]]. He moved to be headmaster at [[Abingdon School]] (1970\u201375), [[Shrewsbury School]] (1975\u201380) and  [[Eton College]] (1980\u201394) and he was Rector of [[Lincoln College, Oxford]] (1994\u20132000). He was chairman of the [[National Lottery (United Kingdom)|Heritage Lottery Fund]] (1998\u20132001), and Provost of [[Eton College]] (2000\u20132009).\n\nAt Fettes, he was [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] [[Tony Blair]]'s housemaster. Blair subsequently named Anderson in a 1997 advertising campaign run by the [[Teacher Training Agency]], entitled 'No one forgets a good teacher'. Because Anderson was Head Master of Eton while [[David Cameron]] and [[Boris Johnson]] were there, he was involved in the education of the heir to the British throne and three British Prime Ministers, as well as [[Justin Welby]], [[Archbishop of Canterbury]].\n\nThe Clarendon Press published Anderson's edition of [[The Journal of Sir Walter Scott]] in 1972 and he became a trustee of Scott's [[Abbotsford House|Abbotsford]] during its refurbishment. He was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Edinburgh]] in 1985 and, in 2002, he was appointed a Knight of the [[Order of the Thistle]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=56780 |date=12 December 2002 |pages=15113\u201315114 }}</ref> \n\nHe retired as Provost of Eton at the end of January 2009, and was succeeded by [[William Waldegrave, Baron Waldegrave of North Hill|William Waldegrave]].\n\nHis other positions included: [[Visitor]] at [[Harris Manchester College, Oxford]]; Member of the Visiting Committee of Harvard University Memorial Church; [[trustee]] of the [[Royal Collection Trust]]; and Chairman of [[Cumberland Lodge]]. He has honorary degrees from the [[University of St Andrews]], Hull, Siena, Birmingham, the [[University of Aberdeen]] and Buckingham.<ref>{{cite web|title=HRH The Duchess of Rothesay joins University 'family'|url=http://www.abdn.ac.uk/news/details-13923.php|publisher=University of Aberdeen}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAnderson was the son of William James Kinloch Anderson and Margaret Gouinlock Harper. He was married to Elizabeth (Poppy) Anderson, daughter of William and Mary Mason of Skipton.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fieldtree.blogspot.com/2012/12/sir-william-eric-kinloch-anderson.html|title=Sir William Eric Kinloch Anderson|last=Field|first=Ron|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-02}}</ref> Their son is [[David Anderson (barrister)|David Anderson Q.C]] (Lord Anderson of Ipswich) and their daughter Kate is married to [[Will Gompertz]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/london-life/will-gompertz-we-are-all-artists-we-just-have-to-believe-it-that-s-what-artists-do-10389894.html|title=Will Gompertz: 'We are all artists. We just have to believe it. That's what artists do'|newspaper=The Evening Standard}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-aca}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Michael William McCrum]]\n| title=[[List of head masters of Eton College|Head Master of Eton College]]\n| years=1980\u20131994\n| after=[[John Lewis (headmaster)|John Lewis]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| before=[[Maurice Shock]]\n| title=[[Rector (college)|Rector]] of [[Lincoln College, Oxford]]\n| years=1994\u20132000 \n| after=[[Paul Langford]]\n}}\n{{succession box\n| title=[[Provost of Eton]]\n| before=[[Antony Acland|Sir Antony Acland]]\n| after= [[William Waldegrave, Baron Waldegrave of North Hill|William Waldegrave]]\n| years=2000\u20132009\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Members of the Order of the Thistle}}\n{{Eton Head Masters}}\n{{Provosts of Eton College}}\n{{Rectors of Lincoln College, Oxford}}\n{{Authority control}}