{"title_page": "Students' Federation of India", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox Union\n|name= Students' Federation of India\n|country= India\n|affiliation= \n|members= 4.3 million (as of 2014-15)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/about-sfi/membership|title=Membership|website=SFICEC|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n|native_name=\n|image= [[File:Students Federation of India.jpg|frameless]]\n|caption       = The Students' Federation of India emblem\n|founded= 1970\n|motto= Independence, Democracy, Socialism\n|current=\n|head=\n|dissolved_date=\n|dissolved_state=\n|merged_into=\n|office= \n|people= [[V. P. Sanu]] (President)<br>Mayukh Biswas (General Secretary)\n|website= {{URL|https://sficec.org}}\n|footnotes=\n}}\n\nThe '''Students' Federation of India''' is an [[India|Indian]] [[student organisation]] affiliated to the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/violence-plagues-college-union-elections-in-west-bengal-728385|title=Violence Plagues College Union Elections in West Bengal|first=Monideepa|last=Banerjie|date=16 January 2015|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Currently, [[V. P. Sanu]] is the National President<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2019/jul/13/why-sfis-v-p-sanu-disbanded-university-college-unit-after-comrade-stabbed-comrade-2003410.html|title='I apologise to people of Kerala': Why SFI's V P Sanu disbanded University College Unit after comrade stabs comrade|first=Parvathi|last=Benu|date=13 July 2019|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> and <nowiki>[[Mayukh Biswas]]</nowiki> is the National General Secretary.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/assam-police-aishe-ghosh-sfi|title=Assam Police Doesn't Want Aishe Ghosh to Address Anti-CAA Meet, Alleges SFI|first=Gaurav|last=Das|date=13 March 2020|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe organization was formed when students assembled in [[Kolkata|Calcutta]] and decided to form a new organization for the purpose of bringing students from across the country together.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sfiwb.org/pdf/History_of_SFI.pdf|title=History_of_SFI}}</ref> The student leaders originally intended to lead discussions on issues including radical education reform, employment, safeguarding, and the expansion of democratic rights.{{CN|date=November 2018}}\n\nThe Students' Federation of India in 2017 lead the student unions of universities in Himachal Pradesh, Delhi, Rajasthan, Gujarat, West Bengal, Tripura, Assam, Odisha, Maharashtra, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu and Kerala.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/state-committees|title=State Committees|website=www.sficec.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/education/jnusu-election-results-2017-counting-starts-10-points-1748067|title=JNUSU Election Results 2017: Left Alliance Leading As Counting Is Underway; 10 Points|work=NDTV.com|access-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>\n\n==Flag==\nThe SFI's flag has a red five-pointed, socialist-style star in the top left corners, on a white background and the words \"Independence\", \"Democracy\" and \"Socialism\" are written, in English or in a local language, one beneath the other, at the bottom right of the flag, also in red. The ratio of length and breadth of the flag is 3:2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/programme/constitution1|title=Constitution|last=User|first=Super|website=www.sficec.org|access-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nIn 2019, a report by Justice (Retd) PK Shamsudin, formed to probe into unlawful activities on college campuses across Kerala, described the presence of \"torture rooms\" operated by the SFI in university campuses across the state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/kerala-a-campus-with-a-torture-room-thiruvananthapurams-university-college-5876072/|title=Kerala: A campus with a \u2018torture room\u2019|first=Shaju|last=Philip|date=2019-08-04|website=The Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/news/kerala/2019/09/03/kerala-colleges-assault-rooms-shamsuddin-commission.html|title=Assault rooms common in Kerala colleges, confirms Shamsuddin commission|website=OnManorama|date=3 September 2020|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> However, the SFI denied these claims.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/kerala-colleges-have-torture-rooms-for-students-who-dont-fall-in-line-with-unions/286641/|title=Kerala colleges have \u2018torture rooms\u2019 for students who don\u2019t fall in line with unions|last=Swamy|first=Rohini|date=2019-09-05|website=ThePrint|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Students' Federation of India}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.sficec.org|name=Official website of SFI Central Executive Committee}}\n* {{Facebook|sficecofficial|SFI Central Executive Committee}}\n\n{{Communist Party of India (Marxist)}}\n\n[[Category:Student organisations in India]]\n[[Category:1970 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Student organizations established in 1970]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of India (Marxist)]]\n[[Category:Volunteer organisations in India]]\n[[Category:Student wings of communist parties of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox Union\n|name= Students' Federation of India\n|country= India\n|affiliation= \n|members= 4.3 million (as of 2014-15)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/about-sfi/membership|title=Membership|website=SFICEC|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref>\n|native_name=\n|image= [[File:Students Federation of India.jpg|frameless]]\n|caption       = The Students' Federation of India emblem\n|founded= 1970\n|motto= Independence, Democracy, Socialism\n|current=\n|head=\n|dissolved_date=\n|dissolved_state=\n|merged_into=\n|office= \n|people= [[V. P. Sanu]] (President)<br>Mayukh Biswas (General Secretary)\n|website= {{URL|https://sficec.org}}\n|footnotes=\n}}\n\nThe '''Students' Federation of India''' is an [[India|Indian]] [[student organisation]] affiliated to the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/violence-plagues-college-union-elections-in-west-bengal-728385|title=Violence Plagues College Union Elections in West Bengal|first=Monideepa|last=Banerjie|date=16 January 2015|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Currently, [[V. P. Sanu]] is the National President<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2019/jul/13/why-sfis-v-p-sanu-disbanded-university-college-unit-after-comrade-stabbed-comrade-2003410.html|title='I apologise to people of Kerala': Why SFI's V P Sanu disbanded University College Unit after comrade stabs comrade|first=Parvathi|last=Benu|date=13 July 2019|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> and Mayukh Biswas is the National General Secretary.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/rights/assam-police-aishe-ghosh-sfi|title=Assam Police Doesn't Want Aishe Ghosh to Address Anti-CAA Meet, Alleges SFI|first=Gaurav|last=Das|date=13 March 2020|website=The Wire|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe organization was formed when students assembled in [[Kolkata|Calcutta]] and decided to form a new organization for the purpose of bringing students from across the country together.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sfiwb.org/pdf/History_of_SFI.pdf|title=History_of_SFI}}</ref> The student leaders originally intended to lead discussions on issues including radical education reform, employment, safeguarding, and the expansion of democratic rights.{{CN|date=November 2018}}\n\nThe Students' Federation of India in 2017 lead the student unions of universities in Himachal Pradesh, Delhi, Rajasthan, Gujarat, West Bengal, Tripura, Assam, Odisha, Maharashtra, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu and Kerala.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/state-committees|title=State Committees|website=www.sficec.org|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/education/jnusu-election-results-2017-counting-starts-10-points-1748067|title=JNUSU Election Results 2017: Left Alliance Leading As Counting Is Underway; 10 Points|work=NDTV.com|access-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>\n\n==Flag==\nThe SFI's flag has a red five-pointed, socialist-style star in the top left corners, on a white background and the words \"Independence\", \"Democracy\" and \"Socialism\" are written, in English or in a local language, one beneath the other, at the bottom right of the flag, also in red. The ratio of length and breadth of the flag is 3:2.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sficec.org/programme/constitution1|title=Constitution|last=User|first=Super|website=www.sficec.org|access-date=2017-09-09}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nIn 2019, a report by Justice (Retd) PK Shamsudin, formed to probe into unlawful activities on college campuses across Kerala, described the presence of \"torture rooms\" operated by the SFI in university campuses across the state.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/kerala-a-campus-with-a-torture-room-thiruvananthapurams-university-college-5876072/|title=Kerala: A campus with a \u2018torture room\u2019|first=Shaju|last=Philip|date=2019-08-04|website=The Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/news/kerala/2019/09/03/kerala-colleges-assault-rooms-shamsuddin-commission.html|title=Assault rooms common in Kerala colleges, confirms Shamsuddin commission|website=OnManorama|date=3 September 2020|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> However, the SFI denied these claims.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/kerala-colleges-have-torture-rooms-for-students-who-dont-fall-in-line-with-unions/286641/|title=Kerala colleges have \u2018torture rooms\u2019 for students who don\u2019t fall in line with unions|last=Swamy|first=Rohini|date=2019-09-05|website=ThePrint|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Students' Federation of India}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.sficec.org|name=Official website of SFI Central Executive Committee}}\n* {{Facebook|sficecofficial|SFI Central Executive Committee}}\n\n{{Communist Party of India (Marxist)}}\n\n[[Category:Student organisations in India]]\n[[Category:1970 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Student organizations established in 1970]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of India (Marxist)]]\n[[Category:Volunteer organisations in India]]\n[[Category:Student wings of communist parties of India]]\n", "name_user": "Leftmovement2018", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Students%27_Federation_of_India"}
